dcterms:description: The Caserta dataset contains 840 instances of the container relocation problem, where the number of stacks and containers per stack can range from 3 to 10, with all stacks having the same initial height. The maximum allowed height of a stack is defined as h + s, where h represents the stack height at the start.
dcterms:title: Caserta Dataset

H. Qin

dcterms:description: The Zhu dataset consists of 125,000 instances of the container relocation problem, featuring between 6 to 10 stacks and between 15 and 69 containers in the bay. Each instance has a specified maximum stack height, which is generally smaller than that in the Caserta dataset, thus restricting the possible relocation moves at the start.
dcterms:title: Zhu Dataset
